The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The assignment response[idx_response] = '\0'; writes a NUL terminator into the allocated buffer but that terminator is never used. ws_send_frame sends the buffer with length idx_response (not idx_response+1), does not call any C-string functions on response, then frees it. Removing this single assignment (and the extra +1 allocation byte) would not change program behaviour, so the statement is dead code and thus violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
